# Deploy after commit + push

This Vercel project is connected to GitHub (`Getu4ever/80-hit-radio`, production branch `main`). Pushes to `main` should create production deployments automatically.

## Required workflow after commit + push

1. Push to `origin/main`.
2. Verify a new Git-triggered production deployment appears for that commit SHA (`npx vercel ls --prod` or Vercel MCP `list_deployments`). Source should be git/github, not only CLI.
3. Wait until Ready and confirm the production alias (`www.rithmgen.co.uk`).

## Fallback

If no Git deployment starts within ~1–2 minutes of the push, deploy manually:

```bash
npx vercel --prod --yes
```

Do not skip verifying production is Ready unless the user explicitly says not to deploy.

If Git auto-deploy stops working again, reconnect with:

```bash
npx vercel git connect https://github.com/Getu4ever/80-hit-radio.git --yes
```
